history.text: Hello
I don't have the movie info, so you'll have to tell me which movie it is.
Do you like animated movies? If you do, you should watch Monsters University. It's the prequel to Pixar's Monsters, Inc.
I do like some animated films.  Who does the voices for this one?
Some of the voice actors consist of John Goodman, Steve Buscemi, John Ratzenberger, Billy Crystal and Bob Peterson.
I like a few of them.  Especially John Goodman.  Does it say if the movie has songs?  I don't like musical cartoons very much.
There is music that is compose by Randy Newman, who has collaborated with Pixar 7 times.
Not a fan of his music.  What can you tell me about the story?
Well it's about two monsters, Sulley and Mike, and their time in college. It tells the story of their journey from being rivals to really good friends.
it's a prequel to the original?  (i haven't seen either one)
Yes, is is the prequel to the Monsters, Inc movie from 2001.
how are the reviews?
They are fairly good. It has an A with CinemaScore and a 79% rating on Rotten Tomatoes!
yeah that's really good.
any more info?
It is. The critics say good things about it too. They say that it really holds true to the spirit of the 2001 movie.
what do the monsters learn about in college?

How to be good scarers - which are monsters that collect childrens screams for energy by entering into the human world at night to scare them. It's not scary at all,
 I promise.
energy from screams.  that's interesting.  too bad for the kids, though.
i suppose i should watch the first one before this one
Yeah, it can seem pretty scary. Its a fun movie though. I would reccomnd watching the first one too if you wanted to get the full effect.
makes sense
any more plot details?
Well remember how I said the main character Sully and Mike were rivals? Well they end up joining this fraternity called Oozma Kappa and compete with other fraternities in different challanges.
what kind of challenges?
Well for example one challange is a bedroom scare simulator.
sounds funny
what are some other characters?
Yeah it's a really fun movie. Oozma Kappa is known for being the weekest fraternity on campus, so it's a little bit of an underdog tale.
i see
Other characters like Randall Boggs and Roz make an apperance.
are those other monsters?
Yes, they are.
we're done!  nice chatting with you
Awesome! Thanks
